  "title": "Can AI Master Econometrics? Evidence from Econometrics AI Agent on Expert-Level Tasks",
  "year": 2026,
  "venue": "arXiv preprint",
  "study_design_description": "The study conducted extensive tests using two real-world datasets: doctoral-level econometrics coursework assignments (18 exercises) and published empirical economics papers (45 randomly selected seminal articles). Performance evaluation compared generated coefficients, standard errors, and p-values against standard solutions from coursework materials or original papers. Two replication standards were defined: perfect replication requires all three errors to be below 1%, while partial replication requires coefficient and standard error gaps below 5%.",
  "primary_task_description": "The first task comprises 18 exercises from a doctoral-level \"Applied Econometrics\" course at the University of Hong Kong, covering OLS & PanelOLS regression, propensity score matching, IV-2SLS regression, Difference-in-Differences (DID) analysis, and Regression Discontinuity Design. The second task consists of test datasets from randomly selected seminal articles in reputable journals, primarily accompanied by Stata-based replication packages. Generated prompts are fed directly to the AI agent, which automatically executes code in a Jupyter kernel and iteratively updates based on error messages.",
  "population_description": "The study evaluates performance through two sets of inquiries: 18 exercises from a doctoral-level econometrics course at the University of Hong Kong with Python-generated standard solutions, and test datasets from randomly selected seminal articles in reputable journals, primarily accompanied by Stata-based replication packages.",
  "arms": [
    {
      "arm_name": "gpt_4o_python",
      "description": "Direct GPT-4o Python code generation: single-round code generation ability of GPT-4o by feeding it structured prompts prefixed with \"use Python language to compute the following task\" and manually executing the generated code.",
      "n": null
    },
    {
      "arm_name": "gpt_4o_stata",
      "description": "Direct GPT-4o Stata code generation: testing LLM code generation in Stata, the most popular software in empirical research. Results are recorded in \".smcl\" log files.",
      "n": null
    },
    {
      "arm_name": "data_interpreter",
      "description": "General-purpose Data Interpreter agent (Hong et al., 2024b): a standard AI agent for data analysis without econometric tool packages.",
      "n": null
    },
    {
      "arm_name": "metricsai",
      "description": "MetricsAI: the proposed specialized AI agent for econometric analysis with econometric tool packages and systematic internal prompts.",
      "n": null
    }
  ],
