  "notes": "This study evaluates MetricsAI, a specialized AI agent for econometric analysis, against three control conditions: GPT-4o Python code generation, GPT-4o Stata code generation, and a general-purpose Data Interpreter agent. Two datasets were tested: 18 doctoral-level coursework assignments and 45 published empirical papers. The paper reports extensive performance metrics including directional replication rates, perfect replication rates (all three errors below 1%), partial replication rates (coefficient and SE gaps below 5%), and detailed error statistics for coefficients, standard errors, and p-values. MetricsAI substantially outperforms all control groups on coursework assignments (96.11% directional replication vs. 21-78% for controls) and published papers (87.78% directional replication vs. 24-75% for controls). The authors note that MetricsAI's performance declines for complex methods like DID and RDD compared to simpler approaches, and results deteriorate when moving from coursework to published paper replication tasks. However, they suggest these limitations can be addressed through enhanced domain knowledge architecture and customized tools.",
  "_paper_id": "2506.00856v3"
}